author: Corbin McGuire corbin@emporia.com
title: Lebo suffers 50-14 loss to Rural Vista
text:
Lebo suffers 50-14 loss to Rural Vista By Corbin McGuire corbin@emporia.com emporiagazette.com | 0 comments 
Lebo was outscored 28-0 in the middle two quarters of a 50-14 loss to Rural Vista Friday night. 
The Wolves got both scores from Conner Gould, who blocked a punt and recovered for a touchdown in the first quarter. Gould broke in for a 2-yard touchdown in the fourth quarter as well. 
“I knew they were going to be good,” Lebo head coach Troy McArthur said. “I thought we’d be able to come out and compete and make it a heck of a lot better game than that with the possibility of coming away with a win, but it just wasn’t going for us tonight.” 
Lebo quarterback Drew Ott went 14 of 32 for 124 yards for the Wolves, who fell to 3-5 and 2-2 in district play. Lebo, which takes on Peabody-Burns next week, still holds an outside chance at the playoffs if it wins next week. 
Lebo 6 0 0 8 — 14 
Rural Vista 8 14 14 14 — 50
